======================================================================
CONNECTION 2: TIGHT-BINDING MODEL / DIRICHLET KERNEL
======================================================================

Q_k = |D_m(2πk/p)|² where D_m is the Dirichlet kernel.
This is the m-slit diffraction intensity pattern!

  p=7, m=3: max|Q_k - D_m²| = 1.78e-15
    Q_1/m² = 0.560991 (coherent fraction)
    Return probability = sum(Q_k)/p = 0.8571 = m(m+1)/(2p) = 0.8571
  p=11, m=5: max|Q_k - D_m²| = 1.78e-15
    Q_1/m² = 0.493742 (coherent fraction)
