======================================================================
CONNECTION 3: COMPRESSED SENSING / L1 vs L∞ NORMS
======================================================================

Walsh Sign Law: H(Paley) = ||ĥ||₁ (L1 norm of Walsh spectrum)
Interval maximizes H via spectral concentration (L∞-like).

In compressed sensing:
  L1 maximizer = maximally spread signal (incoherent measurement)
  L∞ maximizer = maximally concentrated signal (coherent measurement)

The Paley-Interval phase transition at p≈13 is WHERE these diverge!
  Small p: L1 and L∞ maximizers nearly coincide (low dimension)
  Large p: They separate (curse of dimensionality)

