CONNECTION 4: CYCLOTOMIC FIELD RAMIFICATION
======================================================================

disc(Q_1,...,Q_m) = p^{m-1} because Q_k ∈ Q(cos 2π/p)
and disc(Q(cos 2π/p)) = p^{m-1} (conductor-discriminant formula).

  p=5, m=2: disc = p^{m-1} = 5
    prod(2-c_k) = prod 4sin²(πk/p) = 5.000000 ≈ p = 5
  p=7, m=3: disc = p^{m-1} = 49
    prod(2-c_k) = prod 4sin²(πk/p) = 7.000000 ≈ p = 7
  p=11, m=5: disc = p^{m-1} = 14641
    prod(2-c_k) = prod 4sin²(πk/p) = 11.000000 ≈ p = 11
  p=13, m=6: disc = p^{m-1} = 371293
    prod(2-c_k) = prod 4sin²(πk/p) = 13.000000 ≈ p = 13
  p=17, m=8: disc = p^{m-1} = 410338673
    prod(2-c_k) = prod 4sin²(πk/p) = 17.000000 ≈ p = 17
  p=19, m=9: disc = p^{m-1} = 16983563041
    prod(2-c_k) = prod 4sin²(πk/p) = 19.000000 ≈ p = 19

  INSIGHT: The Q_k generate the ring of integers of Q(cos 2π/p).
  Total ramification of p in Q(ζ_p) drives all mod-p structure.

